<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. Huang, K. D. Hyde &amp; Hong Y. Li, Fungal Biology 119 (5): 343" authorityYear="2015" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe multiguttulata" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="multiguttulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diaporthe multiguttulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by ellipsoidal alpha conidia with one large guttulate, and was originally described as an endophyte from healthy branch of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Citrus grandis" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Citrus grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Fujian Province, China (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funbio.2015.02.006" author="Huang, F" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="331 - 347" refId="B19" refString="Huang, F, Udayanga, D, Wang, X, Hou, X, Mei, X, Fu, Y, Hyde, KD, Li, HY, 2015. Endophytic Diaporthe associated with Citrus: A phylogenetic reassessment with seven new species from China. Fungal Biology 119 (5): 331 - 347, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funbio.2015.02.006" title="Endophytic Diaporthe associated with Citrus: A phylogenetic reassessment with seven new species from China." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.funbio.2015.02.006" volume="119" year="2015">Huang et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.77.59999" author="Yang, Q" journalOrPublisher="MycoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="41 - 64" refId="B50" refString="Yang, Q, Jiang, N, Tian, CM, 2021a. New species and records of Diaporthe from Jiangxi Province, China. MycoKeys 77: 41 - 64, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.77.59999" title="New species and records of Diaporthe from Jiangxi Province, China." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.77.59999" volume="77" year="2021 a">Yang et al. (2021a)</bibRefCitation>
identified three isolates from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Citrus maxima" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Citrus maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. multiguttulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="multiguttulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">D. multiguttulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on DNA sequence data and confirmed from the morphological characters. In the present study, isolates (CFCC 53098, CFCC 53099, and CFCC 53100) from an additional specimen were observed and supplemented with beta conidia (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Diaporthe multiguttulata (BJFC-S 1615) a, b habit of conidiomata on twig c transverse section through conidiomata d longitudinal section through conidiomata e-g conidiomata formed on PDA h conidiogenous cells i alpha conidia g beta conidia. Scale bars: 200 μm (b-d); 10 μm (h-j)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.91.84970.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711581" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">4j</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
